Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Lake Tahoe
Description: A majestic, blue freshwater lake in the Sierra Nevada Mountains; which is known to be the second deepest lake in the United States.

Name: Disneyland
Description: Coined “The Happiest Place on Earth”, Disneyland is a large amusement park in Anaheim, where Disney characters and movies are brought to life!

Name: San Francisco
Description: One of California’s largest cities in the United States, San Francisco, is widely known for its “Golden State Bridge”.

Name: Coronado Island
Description: A Bay Island next to San Diego and Mexico’s mainland, popular for its beaches and seafood!

Name: Montebello
Description: A city bordering Los Angeles County, home to a wonderful population of 62,742 people.
